<law type="statute"><section><amendatorysection amended="yes" chaptername="Cities Of The First Class" id="id00" statutenumber="16-213"><bookinfo>Revised Statutes Cumulative Supplement, 2018</bookinfo><statuteno>16-213</statuteno><catchline id="id00">Money; power to borrow.</catchline><para>A city of the first class may borrow money on the credit of the city and pledge the credit, revenue, and public property of the city for the payment thereof when authorized in the manner provided by law.</para></amendatorysection></section><source><para>Laws 1901, c. 18, &#167; 48, XVII, p. 249; </para><para>R.S.1913, &#167; 4829; </para><para>C.S.1922, &#167; 3997; </para><para>C.S.1929, &#167; 16-214; </para><para>R.S.1943, &#167; 16-213; </para><para>Laws 2016, LB704, &#167; 21. </para></source></law>
